title: heritable
text: Let’s work lettuce dataset contains phenotypic measurements downy mildew resistance score 89 lettuce genotypes across 3 locations (environments), 3 replicates.demonstration purposes, use subset single environment (loc == L2), displayed plot .  also access genomic relationship matrix (GRM) calculated 300 genetic markers use narrow-sense heritability.
code: library(dplyr) head(lettuce_phenotypes) #> # A tibble: 6 × 4 #>   loc   gen   rep       y #>   <fct> <fct> <fct> <dbl> #> 1 L1    G1    R1      2   #> 2 L1    G1    R2      2.5 #> 3 L1    G2    R1      1.5 #> 4 L1    G2    R2      2   #> 5 L1    G3    R1      1   #> 6 L1    G3    R2      2  lettuce_subset <- lettuce_phenotypes |>   filter(loc == "L2") # View the structure of the GRM dim(lettuce_GRM) #> [1] 89 89 lettuce_GRM[1:5, 1:5] #>     G1  G2  G3  G4  G5 #> G1 268   9  13  -3 -46 #> G2   9 270 -19 -50 104 #> G3  13 -19 250  21  -5 #> G4  -3 -50  21 281  21 #> G5 -46 104  -5  21 296

title: heritable
text: Broad-sense heritability represents ratio genetic variance phenotypic variance. Genetic variance incorporates additive, epistatic dominance effects. , provided code asreml lme4 fit model genotype random effect. Note heritability estimates data balanced. Use H2() wrapper compute broad-sense heritability. wrapper three key inputs model, lme4 asreml object target, name genotype/varietal/line variable model e.g. "gen" method, method H2 calculation want. default, methods computed. Alternatively want single method, can call method’s function directly. named H2_ prefix, followed method name. Learn method looking help file ?H2_Cullis
code: # Fit an asreml model with genotype as random effect library(asreml) lettuce_asreml <- asreml(   fixed = y ~ rep,   random = ~ gen,   data = lettuce_subset,   trace = FALSE )  # Fit an lme4 model with genotype as random effect library(lme4) lettuce_lme4 <- lmer(y ~ rep + (1 | gen), data = lettuce_subset) # Calculate broad-sense heritability using multiple methods H2(lettuce_asreml, target = "gen", method = c("Standard", "Cullis", "Oakey")) #>  Standard    Cullis     Oakey  #> 0.8294971 0.8294971 0.8294971 H2(lettuce_lme4, target = "gen", method = c("Standard", "Cullis", "Oakey")) #>  Standard    Cullis     Oakey  #> 0.8294971 0.8294971 0.8294971 H2_Cullis(lettuce_asreml, target = "gen") #> [1] 0.8294971 H2_Delta(lettuce_lme4, target = "gen") #> [1] 0.8294971

title: heritable
text: Narrow-sense heritability currently implemented asreml model object native workflow fit GRM using lme4. However possible using extension packages lme4qtl lme4breeding following model, fit lettuce_GRM genomic relationship matrix using asreml::vm() Similar H2(), can use h2() wrapper compute narrow-sense heritability. Remembering specify: model, asreml object target, name genotype/varietal/line variable model e.g. "gen" method, method h2() calculation want. default, function compute available methods. Currently "Oakey" "Delta" implemented h2() Similarly, can call single method sub-functions using prefix h2_ followed method name. calculating pairwise heritability every genotype. See ?h2_Delta_pairwise() learn .
code: # Fit model with GRM for narrow-sense heritability lettuce_asreml_grm <- asreml(   fixed = y ~ loc,   random = ~ vm(gen, lettuce_GRM) + rep,   data = lettuce_phenotypes,   trace = FALSE ) # Calculate narrow-sense heritability h2(lettuce_asreml_grm, target = "gen", method = "Oakey") #> Error in UseMethod("h2"): no applicable method for 'h2' applied to an object of class "asreml" h2_Delta(lettuce_asreml_grm, target = "gen", type = "BLUP") #> Error in UseMethod("h2_Delta"): no applicable method for 'h2_Delta' applied to an object of class "asreml"

title: heritable
text: Depending heritable function, output vary: H2() wrappers return named vector method H2_Delta() return numeric value H2_Delta_by_genotype() return named list according target variable H2_Delta_pairwise() return symmetrical matrix pairwise combinations target interested comparing heritability values across multiple models methods, can leverage tidyverse functions wrangle output dataframe/tibble
code: library(purrr) library(tidyr)  tibble(   model = list(lettuce_lme4, lettuce_asreml) # Include model as a list variable   ) |>   mutate(H2 = map(model, # Apply the `H2()` function over each model object                   ~H2(.x, target = "gen", method = c("Standard", "Delta", "Oakey"))                   )          )|>   unnest_wider(H2) # Expand the output #> # A tibble: 2 × 4 #>   model     Standard Delta Oakey #>   <list>       <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> #> 1 <lmerMod>    0.829 0.829 0.829 #> 2 <asreml>     0.829 0.829 0.829

title: Heritability Estimation from Mixed Models
text: basic example shows calculate broad-sense heritability single environment trial using asreml lme4. H2() function refers broad-sense heritability default, compute available heritability methods . Alternatively, help tidyverse functions, can return measures different models tibble.
code: library(heritable)    fit_asreml <- asreml::asreml(yield ~ rep,     random = ~ gen + rep:block,     data = agridat::john.alpha,     trace = FALSE   )  fit_lme4 <- lme4::lmer(yield ~ rep + (1|gen) + (1|rep:block),                        data = agridat::john.alpha) H2(fit_asreml, target = "gen") #>    Cullis     Oakey    Piepho     Delta  Standard  #> 0.8090841 0.8090841 0.8029760 0.8090841 0.8400648 H2(fit_lme4, target = "gen") #>    Cullis     Oakey    Piepho     Delta  Standard  #> 0.8091338 0.8091338 0.7966375 0.8091338 0.8400678 library(tidyverse) tibble(model = list(fit_lme4, fit_asreml)) |>    mutate(H2 = map(model, ~H2(.x, target = "gen"))) |>    unnest_wider(H2) #> # A tibble: 2 × 6 #>   model     Cullis Oakey Piepho Delta Standard #>   <list>     <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl> <dbl>    <dbl> #> 1 <lmerMod>  0.809 0.809  0.797 0.809    0.840 #> 2 <asreml>   0.809 0.809  0.803 0.809    0.840

title: Calculate Oakey's heritability from model object — H2_Oakey
text: $$H^2_{Oakey} = \frac{\sum_{= n_z+1}^{n_g} \lambda_i}{\sum_{n_g}^{\lambda_i\neq 0}}$$ : \(n_g\) number genotypes \(n_z\) number zero eigenvalues \(\lambda_i\) ith eigenvalue matrix \(I_{m} - G^{-1}C^{gg}\) \(\sigma^2\) variance attributed differences genotype See pages 813 818 reference full derivation explanation Oakey's heritability

text: equation Standard heritability follows: $$H^2_{Standard} = \frac{\sigma^2_g}{\sigma^2_g + \frac{1}{n_g}\sum_{n_g}^{=1} \sigma^2_p / n_{gi}}$$ : \(n_g\) number genotypes \(n_{gi}\) number replicate given genotype \(\sigma_g\) variance attributed genotype differences \(\sigma_p\) variance attributed phenotypic differences

title: Calculate heritability from mixed model object — H2
text: following methods currently implemented broad-sense heritability H2(method = "XX"): "Cullis": $$H^2_{Cullis} = 1 - \frac{PEV^{BLUP}_{\overline\Delta ij}}{2\sigma^2_g}$$ "Oakey": $$H^2_{Oakey} = \frac{\sum_{= n_z+1}^{n_g} \lambda_i}{\sum_{n_g}^{\lambda_i\neq 0}}$$ "Delta": $$H^2_{\Delta ..} = 1 - \frac{PEV^{BLUP}_{\overline\Delta ..}}{2\sigma^2_g}$$ "Piepho": $$H^2_{Piepho} = \frac{\sigma^2_g}{\sigma^2_g + \overline{PEV_{BLUE_g}} / 2}$$ "Standard": $$H^2_{Standard} = \frac{\sigma^2_g}{\sigma^2_g + \frac{1}{n_g}\sum_{n_g}^{=1} \sigma^2_p / n_{gi}}$$ details specific method - take look help file subfunctions ?H2_Cullis
